          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Infrastructure per client</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">~$20/month</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">~$80&ndash;100/month</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">+$60&ndash;80/month per client</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Operational complexity</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Low</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">High</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Significantly more support effort</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4 text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed">
      <strong>When microservices would become appropriate:</strong> when Cloud9 grows a dedicated
      development team (3+ developers working on the tool full-time), when a specific module has
      materially different scaling requirements, or when the MLP or Matured Product phases introduce
      genuinely independent concerns (e.g. an AI service with different compute requirements). At that
      point, the modular monolith architecture makes the extraction straightforward because the
      boundaries are already defined.
    </p>

    <h3 id="section-8-6" class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1B2A4A] mt-8 mb-4">8.6 About BrightKeep (Detailed)</h3>

    <h4 id="section-8-6-our-approach" class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1B2A4A] mt-6 mb-3">Our Approach</h4>

    <p class="mb-4 text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed">
      BrightKeep is a Digital Product &amp; Business Development company. We both build technology
      solutions, and consult on how to build them. We are founded on decades of experience delivering
      in the digital sector across corporate, startup, and consulting environments.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4 text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed">
      We are a product-focussed firm, starting with the problem to solve, not the technology. Our
      engagement process starts with what the customer or business needs, and we shape solutions around
      outcomes rather than tool preferences. We favour pragmatic development &mdash; solutions that are
      understandable, maintainable, and right-sized for where the product&rsquo;s maturity is, with
      clear paths to scale when ready.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4 text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed">
      We work in small, senior teams with short feedback loops. Weekly demos, working software early, and
      clear communication. Our combination of industry and consulting experience means we understand that
